AeroScan — theme.cpp patch: swap the background brand watermark from the Aerospace Village
globe to the Parhelia sundog mark.

FILE: aeroscan-gui/winglet-ui/theme.cpp
FUNCTION: WingletTheme::setColorModePalette(bool darkMode)

Near the end of that function there is one line that loads the watermark and tints it to the
near-black Shadow color. Replace it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
UNIFIED DIFF
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@ WingletTheme::setColorModePalette @@
-    loadMonochromeIcon(&avLogo, ":/images/av_logo.png", QPalette::Shadow);
+    // Parhelia sundog watermark — pre-colored amber, pre-dimmed; load directly (no tint)
+    // so it reads the same in both dark and light mode.
+    avLogo.load(":/images/parhelia_watermark.png");
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

That is the whole required change. `avLogo` is the QPixmap already declared in theme.h and
drawn by renderBgAvLogo(); nothing else needs to change — the label auto-sizes to the new
pixmap (194x256) and stays centered at (300, 245).

================================================================================
OPTIONAL VARIANTS
================================================================================

A) Keep the original tinted pipeline (subtle near-black watermark, Parhelia shape):
   Use the FULL-opacity mark and keep the tint call:
-    loadMonochromeIcon(&avLogo, ":/images/av_logo.png", QPalette::Shadow);
+    loadMonochromeIcon(&avLogo, ":/images/parhelia_mark.png", QPalette::Shadow);

B) Brighter amber watermark (tint full-opacity mark to brand amber instead of pre-dimmed):
-    loadMonochromeIcon(&avLogo, ":/images/av_logo.png", QPalette::Shadow);
+    loadColoredIcon(&avLogo, ":/images/parhelia_mark.png", QColor("#f8af1c"));
   (loadColoredIcon already exists in theme.cpp. Tune brightness by lowering the label's
    opacity in renderBgAvLogo via a QGraphicsOpacityEffect if it's too strong.)

The recommended one-line patch at the top uses parhelia_watermark.png and needs no tint code.
